"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765303","Home Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>Since the commencement of the Joint Fund in November 2014, approximately 50.2 million Euros has been used to build or enhance fencing at the juxtaposed controls in France.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has not provided funding for French policing in the Calais area.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-16T15:08:10.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765303/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765303/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765303/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Undocumented Migrants: Calais","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much funding has been provided to French authorities for (a) security fencing and (b) policing in Calais.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","105470"
