"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765316","Home Office","false","2017-10-11","<p>Overall police spending, including council tax precept, is protected in real terms for the period of Spending Review 2015. Individual PCCs who maximise their precept income are receiving broadly cash flat direct resource funding, including precept, when compared to 2015/16.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-10-11T16:53:57.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765316/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765316/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765316/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 5 September 2017 to Question 6357, which police forces have seen their budgets (a) decrease and (b) increase in real terms since 2015.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","105689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765317","Home Office","false","2017-10-11","<p>All Police Forces in England and Wales are benefiting from Police Transformation Funding, through leading on a project, by partnering with a lead force and/or through a national programme.</p><p>Details of forces receiving PTF funding are published on gov.uk here; <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/police-transformation-fund-successful-bids-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/police-transformation-fund-successful-bids-2016-to-2017</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/police-transformation-fund-successful-bids-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/police-transformation-fund-successful-bids-2017-to-2018</a> .</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-10-11T16:53:46.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765317/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765317/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765317/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Police: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 8 September 2017 to Question 6345, how much each police force has received through the Police Transformation Fund.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","105690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765318","Home Office","false","2017-10-11","<p>Allegations under the Prevention of Terrorism Act 2005 are not held on an individual’s record on the Police National Computer.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-10-11T16:53:12.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765318/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765318/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765318/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether allegations made under the Prevention of Terrorism Act 2005 are held by police on a person's record.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","105696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765319","Home Office","false","2017-10-18","<p>We are proposing an ambitious strategic agreement with the EU that provides a comprehensive framework for our future security, law enforcement and criminal justice cooperation that delivers the capabilities our operational partners need to keep our people safe.</p><p> </p><p>Our proposals are set out in “<em>Security, Law Enforcement and Criminal Justice – a future partnership paper</em>” which was published on 18 September, available on the gov.uk website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/security-law-enforcement-and-criminal-justice-a-future-partnership-paper" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/security-law-enforcement-and-criminal-justice-a-future-partnership-paper</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We are confident that all parties will recognise the value of continued, practical cooperation between the UK and EU on law enforcement and national security.</p><p> </p><p>However, a responsible government should prepare for all potential outcomes, including the unlikely scenario in which no mutually satisfactory agreement can be reached. That is exactly what we are doing across the whole of Government.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-18T14:24:57.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765319/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765319/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765319/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Schengen Agreement: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she has made an assessment of the potential effect of no longer having access to the second generation Schengen Information System on her Department's ability speedily to secure the arrest and extradition of suspects who flee to the EU.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","105757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765320","Home Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>Data on the timeliness of asylum decisions can be found at the following link: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asylum-transparency-data-august-2017" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/asylum-transparency-data-august-2017</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-16T15:14:42.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765320/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765320/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765320/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will place in the Library data on the average waiting times for case resolution for asylum seekers in cases involving torture for each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","105758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765321","Wales Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>The UK Government has spent £162,913 since 2011 relating to the referral of cases to the Supreme Court concerning the legislative competence of the National Assembly for Wales. No costs have been incurred since 2014.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-10-16T15:46:23.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765321/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765321/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765321/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-10-06","Welsh Government: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much the Government has spent from the public purse on undertaking legal cases against the Government of Wales since 2011.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","105759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765322","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>Since 2015, DFID has supported the current electoral process in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). This involved support to increasing democratic representation of women and youth, raising people’s awareness through civic/electoral education, protecting human rights defenders and broadening the Catholic Church’s electoral observation activities. Since February 2017, we have increased our support to civic education and the training of additional independent electoral observers. In addition, we announced that funding would be made available to update the national electoral roll, if all parties were prepared to hold free, fair and timely elections. That offer remains on the table.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-10-13T08:57:29.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765322/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765322/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765322/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Democratic Republic of Congo: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that funding to support the electoral process is effectively disbursed to help stabilise the political climate in the Democratic Republic of Congo; and whether she will take steps to increase funding for civic education and the training of independent electoral observers.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","105560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765323","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>DFID contracts Voluntary Service Overseas to manage the International Citizen Service, deploying 20,000 volunteers from the UK and developing countries between September 2015 and February 2019. Fluctuations in volunteer numbers and expenditure from year to year are a normal feature of the programme.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-13T14:03:09.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765323/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765323/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765323/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","International Citizen Service: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answers of 18 July 2017 to Questions 4979 and 4980, for what reasons there was a reduction in ICS (a) expenditure in financial year 2016-17 and (b) participants in 2016.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","105621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765324","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-11","<p>When assessing the findings and recommendations of this report, the Department for International Development considered: the impartiality of the organisation writing the report; the research methods used and; the existence of clear evidence to support the conclusions in the report. DFID also cross-checked the findings with other international reports to assess whether the evidence, and resulting conclusions, were comparable. Where findings differed from other organisations we assessed whether this was based on credible evidence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-11T17:02:29.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765324/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765324/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765324/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Palestinians: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 13 September 2017 to Question 8642, on Palestinians: schools, what criteria her Department applied in its assessment of the findings and recommendations of the IMPACT-se report on the Palestinian Elementary School Curriculum 2016-17, published in April 2017.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","105565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765325","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-16","<p>In 2015, 10.9% of UK Official Development Assistance (ODA) was made up of core assessed contributions to the EU and spending managed through the European Development Fund (EDF).</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-10-16T07:47:50.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765325/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765325/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765325/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of the UK's international aid budget is managed by the EU.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","105629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765326","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>The full implications of this Amendment are not yet clear. The UK is aware of NGOs who have expressed concerns. We will be paying close attention to any potential impact on the work of our partners and monitoring the situation as it develops.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-13T14:02:23.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765326/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765326/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765326/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Israel: Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what information her Department holds of instances when the work of organisations in receipt of its funding or other support has been materially affected by the enforcement by the Government of Israel of Amendment 27 to the Entry into Israel law of 1952.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","105646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765327","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>The full implications of this Amendment are not yet clear. DFID holds regular conversations with our partner organisations in the Occupied Palestinian Territories (OPTs) about issues affecting their work and the development of the OPTs. We will continue to monitor this situation as it develops.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-13T14:02:45.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765327/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765327/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765327/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Palestinians: Immigration Controls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will make an assessment of the potential implications for the development of the Palestinian Territories of Amendment 27 to the Entry into Israel law of 1952.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","105643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765328","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>The increase in the number of applications to join DFID on loan is due to an increase in the number of jobs advertised across government on loan or permanent transfer.</p><p> </p><p>DFID’s aim is to widen candidate attributes and enhance the capability and experience of our staff, building a more inclusive organisation to meet the changing priorities of our work.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-10-13T13:14:14.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765328/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765328/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Department for International Development: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 11 September 2017 to Question 7998, on secondments, what assessment she has made of the reasons for the rise in applications in 2017.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","105436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765329","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>Since 2012 the UK has pledged £2.46 billion in response to the Syria crisis, the UK’s largest ever response to a single humanitarian crisis. As well as supporting children with food, shelter and healthcare, the UK helped to launch UNICEF’s No Lost Generation Initiative, which provides education, protection, and mental health support for children in Syria and neighbouring countries. At the 2016 London Syria Conference we did not make a specific pledge for education inside Syria, but in 2016/17 alone DFID helped ensure that over 350,000 children accessed formal primary and secondary education in Syria, and that over 80,000 benefitted from non-formal education.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-13T14:03:40.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765329/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765329/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765329/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","Syria: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment her Department has made of progress towards the amount the Government pledged for education in Syria at the London donor conference in February 2016.","false","Biography information for Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","City of Durham","Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","105487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765330","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-16","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate costs.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-10-16T15:14:33.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765330/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765330/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765330/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-06","Criminal Injuries Compensation: Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many child victims of sexual abuse have been denied compensation by the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority (CICA) since 1996 on the grounds that (a) they had unspent convictions, (b) they had not falsely given consent as a result of being groomed and (c) made an application to CICA more than two years after (i) the date of the assault and (ii) the time they reported it to the police and (iii) if they were under 18 at the time of the incident, failed to make the complaint by their 20th birthday.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","105485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765331","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-18","<p>Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) received additional funding which totalled £37.15m in the 2016/17 financial year. CRCs also received an interim uplift which totalled £22m in the early months of the 2017/18 financial year. These payments were made for a variety of reasons and cannot be broken down by CRC because the information is commercially sensitive. Furthermore, agreements were made with CRCs on a case-by-case basis to enable them to re-invest contractual payment deductions in key areas of the business and improve services.</p><p> </p><p>We have made changes to how CRCs are paid for future years so they can focus on activities that best rehabilitate offenders and keep society safe. This additional investment will see projected payments to providers being no higher than originally budgeted for at the time of the reforms.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","105458 ; 105459 ; 105461","2017-10-18T16:06:39.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765331/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765331/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-06","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much additional funding he plans for each community rehabilitation company to receive in 2017.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","105460"
