"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765454","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-11","<p>We have had Cabinet level engagement with the US Administration and Canadian government. We continue to make efforts alongside the Canadian government to get Boeing into discussions to resolve the case. Ministers across government together with officials have engaged with the US and Canadian administrations and at Bombardier in Canada and Belfast to help in bringing this issue to a solution.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-11T12:44:34.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765454/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765454/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765454/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-06","Department for International Trade: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 15 September 2017 to Question 9154, whether he discussed the Bombardier-Boeing dispute with Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross during his visit to the US in July 2017.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","106245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765455","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Prime Minster recently announced the official theme for the 2018 Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting – 'Towards a Common Future' – and the four key goals which were agreed at a meeting of Commonwealth Foreign Ministers: to build a fairer, more prosperous, more secure and more sustainable future for all Commonwealth citizens.</p><p>We are currently in the process of engaging with the Commonwealth Secretariat, other member states and organisations from across the Commonwealth to agree the agenda for next year's Heads of Government meeting. The Government remains committed to supporting the most marginalised in society and tackling mental illness.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","106083","2017-10-16T16:29:04.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765455/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765455/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765455/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-06","Commonwealth: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether mental health will be included on the agenda for the Commonwealth Summit 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","106082"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765456","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Prime Minster recently announced the official theme for the 2018 Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting – 'Towards a Common Future' – and the four key goals which were agreed at a meeting of Commonwealth Foreign Ministers: to build a fairer, more prosperous, more secure and more sustainable future for all Commonwealth citizens.</p><p>We are currently in the process of engaging with the Commonwealth Secretariat, other member states and organisations from across the Commonwealth to agree the agenda for next year's Heads of Government meeting. The Government remains committed to supporting the most marginalised in society and tackling mental illness.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","106082","2017-10-16T16:29:04.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765456/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765456/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765456/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-06","Commonwealth: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government plans to raise the issue of mental health and discrimination against people with mental illness at the Commonwealth Summit 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","106083"
