"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765459","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>As Minister for Arts, Heritage and Tourism, I would be delighted to visit the National Museum of the Royal Navy in Hartlepool, subject to diary commitments. Hartlepool has a fantastic maritime and industrial heritage and the museum plays an important role in telling the story of the North East’s contribution to Royal Navy heritage.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-10-16T10:24:16.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765459/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765459/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765459/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-06","Royal Naval Museum: Hartlepool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if she will visit the National Museum of the Royal Navy in Hartlepool.","false","Biography information for Mike Hill","Hartlepool","Mike Hill","105810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765460","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-16","<p>Figures on public sector spend at a regional and national level are part of the Government’s Country and Regional Analysis (CRA) statistics. These statistics attempt to allocate the spending according to where the benefits of that spend are accrued.</p><p> </p><p>The latest CRA statistics suggest that in 2015-16 there was £182 of capital expenditure on transport per head of population by central and local governments and other public bodies for the North East of England. This information is available for government office regions only, and therefore is unavailable for the Hartlepool constituency.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-10-16T12:08:23.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765460/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765460/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765460/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-06","Transport: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the capital spend on transport per head of population in (a) the North Eastand (b) Hartlepool constituency in the last 12 months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mike Hill","Hartlepool","Mike Hill","105744"
